  "doc_id": "43376",
  "text": "The overall marginal and internal gaps were both highly acceptable, and the greater standard deviations are believed to be due to the accumulation of optical diffraction, [CITATION_1] investment expansion processes, shrinkage of the metal coping in the casting process, or human error in the fabrication process. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Compared to multilayer additive manufacturing using UV photopolymer processing methods in the field of dentistry, m-SLA produces excellent results with respect to the marginal gap. However, studies are yet to be performed regarding the accuracy with different quantities of resin copings on the build platform.",
